  "text": "Ageing is associated with changes in body composition and involuntary weight loss. Specifically, a large component of involuntary weight loss in older adults is fat-free mass (FFM) and is highly predictive of increased morbidity and mortality (1 -3) . Losses in lean muscle occur at a rate of approximately 1 -2 % per year following the age of 50 years [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
